26/12/2002
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Ion Iliescu described the invitation for NATO membership and progress in the EU accession talks as major achievements and challenges for the nation.
In a year-end speech Tuesday (24 December), he noted that EU and NATO integration would continue to be the two key goals in the new year.
Iliescu added that the government must maintain dialogue with foreign partners to complete the NATO accession process and close all EU negotiations chapters in 2004.
(Rompres, Romanian TV -- 24/12/02)
